I’d like to talk about a job that I wouldn’t like to do, which is being a coach driver.

I first thought about this when I was in high school. At that time, I took a sleeper bus with some of my close friends to visit Da Lat, which is quite far from where I live. It took around seven hours to get there, so we had to leave quite late at night, at around 11 PM.

During the trip, I sat near the driver and had a short conversation with him. He told me that he didn’t really enjoy his job, but he had to keep doing it to support his family. That conversation left a strong impression on me.

One reason I wouldn’t like this job is because of the health risks. Drivers often have to stay awake all night, and some rely on energy drinks to keep going, which can be harmful in the long run. Also, sitting for long hours and not getting enough sleep can lead to serious health problems.

Another reason is the working schedule. Coach drivers usually work at night or during holidays, which means they don’t have much time to spend with their families or friends. Personally, I think that’s a big downside.

I even have a friend whose father sadly passed away from a stroke while working as a driver, which made me realize how demanding and risky this job can be.

Overall, although this job is important, I don’t think it’s something I would enjoy doing because of the pressure and lifestyle.
